 TWO pastors have been arrested in Kaduna for holding church services last Sunday, in violation of the lockdown order. Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs Samuel Aruwan said in a statement on Tuesday that Ifeanyi Ojonu and Giniki Okafor who allegedly held church service at Sabon Tasha area of Chikun Local Government Area of the state, were arraigned before a Chief Magistrate Court on Monday. They were charged with criminal conspiracy and disobedience to an order duly promulgated by a public servant, he said.      